#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:4
msgid "Data type API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:8
msgid ""
"The standard array can have 25 different data types (and has some support "
"for adding your own types). These data types all have an enumerated type, an "
"enumerated type-character, and a corresponding array scalar Python type "
"object (placed in a hierarchy). There are also standard C typedefs to make "
"it easier to manipulate elements of the given data type. For the numeric "
"types, there are also bit-width equivalent C typedefs and named typenumbers "
"that make it easier to select the precision desired."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:19
msgid ""
"The names for the types in c code follows c naming conventions more closely. "
"The Python names for these types follow Python conventions.  Thus, :c:data:"
"`NPY_FLOAT` picks up a 32-bit float in C, but :class:`numpy.float64` in "
"Python corresponds to a 64-bit double. The bit-width names can be used in "
"both Python and C for clarity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:28
msgid "Enumerated types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:32
msgid ""
"There is a list of enumerated types defined providing the basic 25 data "
"types plus some useful generic names. Whenever the code requires a type "
"number, one of these enumerated types is requested. The types are all called "
"``NPY_{NAME}``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:39
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for the boolean type, stored as one byte. It may only "
"be set to the values 0 and 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:45
msgid "The enumeration value for an 8-bit/1-byte signed integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:50
msgid "The enumeration value for a 16-bit/2-byte signed integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:55
msgid "The enumeration value for a 32-bit/4-byte signed integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:59
msgid ""
"Equivalent to either NPY_INT or NPY_LONGLONG, depending on the platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:65
msgid "The enumeration value for a 64-bit/8-byte signed integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:70
msgid "The enumeration value for an 8-bit/1-byte unsigned integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:75
msgid "The enumeration value for a 16-bit/2-byte unsigned integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:80
msgid "The enumeration value for a 32-bit/4-byte unsigned integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:84
msgid ""
"Equivalent to either NPY_UINT or NPY_ULONGLONG, depending on the platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:90
msgid "The enumeration value for a 64-bit/8-byte unsigned integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:95
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a 16-bit/2-byte IEEE 754-2008 compatible floating "
"point type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:101
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a 32-bit/4-byte IEEE 754 compatible floating point "
"type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:107
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a 64-bit/8-byte IEEE 754 compatible floating point "
"type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:112
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a platform-specific floating point type which is "
"at least as large as NPY_DOUBLE, but larger on many platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:118
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a 64-bit/8-byte complex type made up of two "
"NPY_FLOAT values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:124
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a 128-bit/16-byte complex type made up of two "
"NPY_DOUBLE values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:129
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a platform-specific complex floating point type "
"which is made up of two NPY_LONGDOUBLE values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:134
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a data type which holds dates or datetimes with a "
"precision based on selectable date or time units."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:139
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a data type which holds lengths of times in "
"integers of selectable date or time units."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:144
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for null-padded byte strings of a selectable size. The "
"strings have a fixed maximum size within a given array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:149
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for UCS4 strings of a selectable size. The strings "
"have a fixed maximum size within a given array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:154
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for UTF-8 variable-width strings. Note that this dtype "
"holds an array of references, with string data stored outside of the array "
"buffer. Use the C API for working with numpy variable-width static strings "
"to access the string data in each array entry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:160
msgid "This DType is new-style and is not included in ``NPY_NTYPES_LEGACY``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:164
msgid "The enumeration value for references to arbitrary Python objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:168
msgid ""
"Primarily used to hold struct dtypes, but can contain arbitrary binary data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:171
msgid "Some useful aliases of the above types are"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:175
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for a signed integer of type ``Py_ssize_t`` (same as "
"``ssize_t`` if defined). This is the type used by all arrays of indices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:179
msgid ""
"Previously, this was the same as ``intptr_t`` (same size as a pointer).  In "
"practice, this is identical except on very niche platforms. You can use the "
"``'p'`` character code for the pointer meaning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:187
msgid ""
"The enumeration value for an unsigned integer type that is identical to a "
"``size_t``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:190
msgid ""
"Previously, this was the same as ``uintptr_t`` (same size as a pointer).  In "
"practice, this is identical except on very niche platforms. You can use the "
"``'P'`` character code for the pointer meaning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:198
msgid ""
"The enumeration value of the type used for masks, such as with the :c:data:"
"`NPY_ITER_ARRAYMASK` iterator flag. This is equivalent to :c:data:"
"`NPY_UINT8`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:204
msgid ""
"The default type to use when no dtype is explicitly specified, for example "
"when calling np.zero(shape). This is equivalent to :c:data:`NPY_DOUBLE`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:208
msgid "Other useful related constants are"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:212
msgid ""
"The number of built-in NumPy types written using the legacy DType system. "
"New NumPy dtypes will be written using the new DType API and may not "
"function in the same manner as legacy DTypes. Use this macro if you want to "
"handle legacy DTypes using different code paths or if you do not want to "
"update code that uses ``NPY_NTYPES_LEGACY`` and does not work correctly with "
"new DTypes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:220
msgid ""
"Newly added DTypes such as ``NPY_VSTRING`` will not be counted in "
"``NPY_NTYPES_LEGACY``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:225
msgid "A signal value guaranteed not to be a valid type enumeration number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:229
msgid ""
"The start of type numbers used for legacy Custom Data types. New-style user "
"DTypes currently are currently *not* assigned a type-number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:233
msgid ""
"The total number of user dtypes is limited to below ``NPY_VSTRING``. Higher "
"numbers are reserved to future new-style DType use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:236
msgid ""
"The various character codes indicating certain types are also part of an "
"enumerated list. References to type characters (should they be needed at "
"all) should always use these enumerations. The form of them is ``NPY_{NAME}"
"LTR`` where ``{NAME}`` can be"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:241
msgid ""
"**BOOL**, **BYTE**, **UBYTE**, **SHORT**, **USHORT**, **INT**, **UINT**, "
"**LONG**, **ULONG**, **LONGLONG**, **ULONGLONG**, **HALF**, **FLOAT**, "
"**DOUBLE**, **LONGDOUBLE**, **CFLOAT**, **CDOUBLE**, **CLONGDOUBLE**, "
"**DATETIME**, **TIMEDELTA**, **OBJECT**, **STRING**, **UNICODE**, "
"**VSTRING**, **VOID**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:247
msgid "**INTP**, **UINTP**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:249
msgid "**GENBOOL**, **SIGNED**, **UNSIGNED**, **FLOATING**, **COMPLEX**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/dtype.rst:251
msgid ""
"The latter group of ``{NAME}s`` corresponds to letters used in the array "
"interface typestring specification."
msgstr ""

